<title>Marc Duiker — Isometric Parallax (Wireframe)</title>
<meta name="description" content="Homepage and article-page design for marcduiker.dev: paper ground with large wireframe 3D solids drifting down the full page, plus cursor parallax.">

<style>
  :root {
    --gold:    #feae34;
    --gold-dk: #d98e16;
    --blue:    #0095e9;
    --blue-dk: #0072b8;
    --darkhi:  #124e89;
    --yellow:  #fee761;
    --yellow-dk:#e6cc34;
    --ink:     #161616;
    --paper:   #f6f4ef;
    --g500:    #636363;
    --g600:    #484848;

    --font-slab: "Rockwell", "Roboto Slab", Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
    --font-sans: Roboto, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
    --font-mono: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { margin: 0; background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink); font-family: var(--font-sans); overflow-x: hidden; }
  a { color: inherit; }
  img { max-width: 100%; }

  #bg { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; z-index: 0; pointer-events: none; }
  .iso-nav, .iso-hero, .iso-sec, .iso-foot, .article, .page-content, .page-hero, .page-section { position: relative; z-index: 2; }

  /* ---------- nav ---------- */
  .iso-nav {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.4rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
    max-width: 1160px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1.4rem 1.4rem .4rem;
  }
  .iso-nav .logo { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem; letter-spacing: -.02ch; text-decoration: none; }
  .iso-nav .logo .dot { color: var(--gold); }
  .iso-nav nav { display: flex; gap: 1.3rem; margin-left: auto; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .iso-nav nav a { text-decoration: none; font-size: .82rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--g600); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06ch; }
  .iso-nav nav a:hover, .iso-nav nav a.active { color: var(--blue); }

  /* ---------- hero ---------- */
  .iso-hero {
    max-width: 1160px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.4rem 5rem; min-height: 66vh;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center;
  }
  .page-hero {
    max-width: 1160px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.4rem 3rem; min-height: 50vh;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center;
  }
  .iso-hero .badge, .page-hero .badge, .ameta .tag {
    display: inline-block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .72rem;
    letter-spacing: .14ch; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--blue-dk);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 999px; padding: .3rem .8rem;
    background: rgba(246,244,239,.7);
  }
  .iso-hero .badge { align-self: flex-start; margin-bottom: 1.6rem; }
  .page-hero .badge { align-self: flex-start; margin-bottom: 1.6rem; }
  .iso-hero h1, .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 5rem); line-height: .98; margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    max-width: 17ch; text-wrap: balance; letter-spacing: -.02ch;
  }
  .iso-hero h1 .hl { background: var(--yellow); padding: 0 .12em; box-decoration-break: clone; -webkit-box-decoration-break: clone; }
  .iso-hero h1 .heart { color: var(--gold); }
  .iso-hero p, .page-hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; max-width: 42ch; color: var(--g600); line-height: 1.55; margin: 0; }

  /* ---------- section heads ---------- */
  .iso-sec { max-width: 1160px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1.5rem 1.4rem; }
  .iso-sechead { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 1.4rem; }
  .iso-sechead h2 { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin: 0; }
  .iso-sechead a { text-decoration: none; }
  .iso-sechead .arrow { color: var(--blue); font-weight: 700; align-self: center; }
  .iso-sechead .rule { flex: 1; height: 3px; background: var(--ink); align-self: center; }

  /* ---------- cards / tiles ---------- */
  .cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1.4rem; }
  .card {
    background: #fff; border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem; box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    transition: transform .14s ease, box-shadow .14s ease; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .5rem; cursor: pointer;
  }
  .card:hover { transform: translate(-3px,-3px); box-shadow: 12px 12px 0 var(--blue); }
  .card .knum { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .72rem; color: var(--gold-dk); letter-spacing: .1ch; }
  .card h3 { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0; line-height: 1.15; }
  .card .m { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .72rem; color: var(--g500); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .card .m b { color: var(--blue-dk); font-weight: 400; }

  .pxgrid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  .pxtile {
    aspect-ratio: 1; border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px; background: #fff;
    box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 var(--ink); display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: .4rem; padding: .5rem; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    transition: transform .14s ease, box-shadow .14s ease;
  }
  .pxtile:hover { transform: translate(-2px,-2px); box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--gold); }
  .pxtile svg { width: 52%; height: 52%; }
  .pxtile span { font-size: .62rem; text-align: center; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--g600); font-weight: 500; }

  .gen3 { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.4rem; }
  .gentile {
    aspect-ratio: 4/3; border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink); position: relative; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    transition: transform .14s ease, box-shadow .14s ease;
  }
  .gentile:hover { transform: translate(-3px,-3px); box-shadow: 10px 10px 0 var(--yellow-dk); }
  .gentile svg { position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .gentile span { position: absolute; left: 0; bottom: 0; right: 0; background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); font-size: .74rem; padding: .4rem .6rem; font-weight: 500; }

  /* ---------- footer ---------- */
  .iso-foot {
    max-width: 1160px; margin: 2rem auto 0; padding: 1.4rem; border-top: 3px solid var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .74rem; color: var(--g600);
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .6rem;
  }
  .iso-foot b { color: var(--ink); }
  .iso-pad { height: 48px; }

  /* ============================================================
     ARTICLE DETAIL PAGE
     ============================================================ */
  .article {
    width: min(988px, calc(100% - 2.8rem));
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
    padding: 2.6rem 2.2rem 2.8rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 10px 10px 0 var(--ink);
  }
  .article .back {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .78rem; text-decoration: none; color: var(--blue-dk);
    display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
  }
  .article .back:hover { color: var(--blue); }
  .ameta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: .9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .76rem; color: var(--g500); }
  .ameta .tag { color: var(--blue-dk); }
  .ameta .dot { width: 4px; height: 4px; background: var(--gold); border-radius: 50%; }
  .article h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.3rem);
    line-height: 1.04; margin: 0 0 1.2rem; letter-spacing: -.02ch; text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .article .lead { font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--g600); margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .article .hr-rule { height: 3px; background: var(--ink); margin: 1.8rem 0 2rem; }

  .prose { font-size: 1.06rem; line-height: 1.72; color: #262626; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.55rem; margin: 2.4rem 0 .9rem; line-height: 1.15; }
  .prose h3 { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 2rem 0 .8rem; line-height: 1.2; }
  .prose a { color: var(--blue-dk); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .prose a:hover { color: var(--blue); }
  .prose ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose li { margin: .35rem 0; }
  .prose strong { font-weight: 700; }
  .prose em { font-style: italic; }
  .prose code { font-family: var(--font-mono); background: rgba(0,149,233,.12); padding: .12em .4em; border-radius: 3px; font-size: .88em; }
  .prose blockquote {
    margin: 1.8rem 0; padding: 1rem 1.3rem; border-left: 5px solid var(--gold);
    background: rgba(254,231,97,.22); font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .prose blockquote cite { display: block; margin-top: .5rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .76rem; font-style: normal; color: var(--g500); }
  pre.code {
    background: var(--ink); color: #dfe6ee; border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--darkhi); padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 1.6rem; overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .82rem; line-height: 1.55;
  }
  pre.code .k { color: var(--gold); }
  pre.code .s { color: var(--yellow); }
  pre.code .c { color: #7f8aa0; }

  .atags { display: flex; gap: .6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 2.2rem 0 0; }
  .atags a {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .72rem; text-decoration: none; color: var(--blue-dk);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 999px; padding: .25rem .7rem;
  }
  .atags a:hover { background: var(--blue); color: #fff; }

  .author {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem;
    background: var(--paper); border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink);
  }
  .author .av {
    width: 54px; height: 54px; flex: none; border: 2px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 50%;
    display: grid; place-items: center; font-family: var(--font-slab); font-weight: 700; background: var(--gold); color: var(--ink);
  }
  .author b { font-family: var(--font-slab); }
  .author p { margin: .2rem 0 0; font-size: .86rem; color: var(--g600); line-height: 1.4; }

  .pager { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.2rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0; }
  .pager a { text-decoration: none; }
  .pager .lbl { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .7rem; color: var(--gold-dk); letter-spacing: .08ch; display: block; margin-bottom: .3rem; }
  .pager .ptitle { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.2; }
  .pager .next { text-align: right; }
  .pager .card { background: var(--paper); }

  /* ============================================================
     PAGE CONTENT (About, Pixel Art, Generative Art)
     ============================================================ */
  .page-content {
    width: min(988px, calc(100% - 2.8rem));
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
    padding: 2.6rem 2.2rem 2.8rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 10px 10px 0 var(--ink);
  }
  .page-content .back {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .78rem; text-decoration: none; color: var(--blue-dk);
    display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
  }
  .page-content .back:hover { color: var(--blue); }
  .page-content h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.3rem);
    line-height: 1.04; margin: 0 0 1.2rem; letter-spacing: -.02ch; text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .page-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.55rem; margin: 2.4rem 0 .9rem; line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .page-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 2rem 0 .8rem; line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .page-content p { font-size: 1.06rem; line-height: 1.72; color: #262626; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .page-content a { color: var(--blue-dk); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .page-content a:hover { color: var(--blue); }
  .page-content strong { font-weight: 700; }
  .page-content em { font-style: italic; }
  .page-content ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .page-content li { margin: .35rem 0; }
  .page-content code { font-family: var(--font-mono); background: rgba(0,149,233,.12); padding: .12em .4em; border-radius: 3px; font-size: .88em; }
  .page-content .lead { font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--g600); margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .page-content .hr-rule { height: 3px; background: var(--ink); margin: 1.8rem 0 2rem; }

  /* Page Section - for H2 as articles */
  .page-section {
    width: min(988px, calc(100% - 2.8rem));
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.8rem 2.2rem 2rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink);
  }
  .page-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.55rem; margin: 0 0 .9rem; line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .page-section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 1.6rem 0 .8rem; line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .page-section p { font-size: 1.06rem; line-height: 1.72; color: #262626; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .page-section a { color: var(--blue-dk); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .page-section a:hover { color: var(--blue); }
  .page-section ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .page-section li { margin: .35rem 0; }

  /* Platforms list styling */
  .platforms-list {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .platform-card {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: .8rem; padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--paper); border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 var(--ink); text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    transition: transform .14s ease, box-shadow .14s ease;
  }
  .platform-card:hover { transform: translate(-3px,-3px); box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--gold); }
  .platform-card svg { width: 24px; height: 24px; flex: none; }
  .platform-card span { font-size: .95rem; font-weight: 500; }

  /* Pixel Art Gallery */
  .pixel-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1.4rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .pixel-card {
    background: var(--paper); border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.2rem; box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink);
    transition: transform .14s ease, box-shadow .14s ease; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .8rem;
  }
  .pixel-card:hover { transform: translate(-3px,-3px); box-shadow: 10px 10px 0 var(--gold); }
  .pixel-card svg { width: 100%; height: auto; max-height: 180px; }
  .pixel-card h4 { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1rem; margin: 0; }
  .pixel-card .desc { font-size: .86rem; color: var(--g600); margin: 0; }

  /* Generative Art Gallery */
  .gen-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.4rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .gen-card {
    background: var(--paper); border: 2.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink);
    transition: transform .14s ease, box-shadow .14s ease; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
  }
  .gen-card:hover { transform: translate(-3px,-3px); box-shadow: 10px 10px 0 var(--yellow-dk); }
  .gen-card svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; aspect-ratio: 4/3; }
  .gen-card .content { padding: 1rem; }
  .gen-card h4 { font-family: var(--font-slab); font-size: 1rem; margin: 0 0 .4rem; }
  .gen-card .link { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .78rem; color: var(--blue-dk); text-decoration: none; }
  .gen-card .link:hover { color: var(--blue); }

  /* Iframe styling */
  .page-content iframe, .page-section iframe { max-width: 100%; height: auto; border: none; margin: 1.5rem 0; }

  /* ---------- review controls ---------- */
  .ctl { position: fixed; z-index: 50; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .7rem; letter-spacing: .04ch; }
  .viewswitch { left: 14px; bottom: 14px; display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .viewswitch button {
    background: var(--paper); color: var(--g600); border: 1.5px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 999px; padding: .45rem .8rem; cursor: pointer; font: inherit;
  }
  .viewswitch button[aria-pressed="true"] { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); }
  #motionToggle {
    right: 14px; bottom: 14px; background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 999px; padding: .45rem .8rem; cursor: pointer; font: inherit;
  }
  #motionToggle:hover { background: var(--darkhi); border-color: var(--darkhi); }
  .ctl button:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--gold); outline-offset: 2px; }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pxgrid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
    .gen3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pixel-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .gen-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pager { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .article, .page-content, .page-section { padding: 1.8rem 1.3rem 2rem; }
    .platforms-list { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .pxgrid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .viewswitch { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
    .page-hero { min-height: 40vh; padding: 2rem 1.4rem 2rem; }
  }
</style>

<canvas id="bg" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>

<!-- ===================== HOME ===================== -->
<div id="page-home">
  <div class="iso-nav">
    <a class="logo" href="#" data-view="home">Marc Duiker<span class="dot">.</span></a>
    <nav>
      <a href="#" class="active" data-view="article">Articles</a><a href="#" data-view="generative-art">Generative Art</a><a href="#" data-view="pixel-art">Pixel Art</a><a href="#" data-view="about">About</a>
    </nav>
  </div>

  <header class="iso-hero">
    <span class="badge">Creative Technologist</span>
    <h1>I <span class="heart">❤</span> OSS, <span class="hl">developer experience</span>, pixel art &amp; generative art.</h1>
    <p>Building in the open and helping people achieve more every day — with a little geometry drifting in the background.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="iso-sec">
    <div class="iso-sechead">
      <h2><a href="#" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">Latest Articles</a></h2>
      <a href="#" class="arrow" data-view="article" aria-label="All articles">→</a>
      <span class="rule"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="cards">
      <a class="card" href="#" data-view="article"><span class="knum">001</span><h3>What is publiccode.yml?</h3><span class="m">2026.06.24 · <b>OSS</b></span></a>
      <a class="card" href="#"><span class="knum">002</span><h3>Getting Started with Codeberg</h3><span class="m">2026.06.10 · <b>OSS</b></span></a>
      <a class="card" href="#"><span class="knum">003</span><h3>Speaking at DevSum 2026</h3><span class="m">2026.05.28 · <b>Talk</b></span></a>
      <a class="card" href="#"><span class="knum">004</span><h3>Speaking at Update Conference Krakow 2026</h3><span class="m">2026.05.15 · <b>Talk</b></span></a>
      <a class="card" href="#"><span class="knum">005</span><h3>Speaking at Techorama Belgium 2026</h3><span class="m">2026.05.02 · <b>Talk</b></span></a>
      <a class="card" href="#"><span class="knum">006</span><h3>Managing the Dapr Kiosk at KubeCon EU 2026</h3><span class="m">2026.04.20 · <b>Dapr</b></span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="iso-sec">
    <div class="iso-sechead">
      <h2><a href="#" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">Latest Pixel Art</a></h2>
      <a href="#" class="arrow" data-view="pixel-art">→</a>
      <span class="rule"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="pxgrid" id="px"></div>
  </section>

  <section class="iso-sec">
    <div class="iso-sechead">
      <h2><a href="#" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">Latest Generative Art</a></h2>
      <a href="#" class="arrow" data-view="generative-art">→</a>
      <span class="rule"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="gen3" id="gen"></div>
  </section>

  <footer class="iso-foot">
    <span>Built in the open · <b>marcduiker.dev</b></span>
    <span>Wireframe solids drift the full page — your cursor nudges them.</span>
    <span>&copy; 2026 <b>Marc Duiker</b></span>
  </footer>
  <div class="iso-pad"></div>
</div>

<!-- ===================== ARTICLE DETAIL ===================== -->
<div id="page-article" style="display:none">
  <div class="iso-nav">
    <a class="logo" href="#" data-view="home">Marc Duiker<span class="dot">.</span></a>
    <nav>
      <a href="#" class="active" data-view="article">Articles</a><a href="#" data-view="generative-art">Generative Art</a><a href="#" data-view="pixel-art">Pixel Art</a><a href="#" data-view="about">About</a>
    </nav>
  </div>

  <article class="article">
    <a class="back" href="#" data-view="home">← All articles</a>
    <div class="ameta">
      <span class="tag">OSS</span>
      <span>2026.06.24</span><span class="dot"></span>
      <span>13 min read</span><span class="dot"></span>
      <span>by Marc Duiker</span>
    </div>
    <h1>What is publiccode.yml?</h1>
    <p class="lead">Exploring the publiccode.yml standard that helps public administrations make their software discoverable and reusable.</p>
    <div class="hr-rule"></div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p><strong>TLDR:</strong> <code>publiccode.yml</code> is a metadata standard in YAML format that describes software created by or for public administrations. Placed in the root of a repository, it makes public software easily discoverable and reusable by both humans and machines.</p>

      <hr style="margin: 2rem 0; border: 0; height: 2px; background: var(--ink);" />

      <p>Last week I attended a meetup of <a href="https://developer.overheid.nl/">developer.overheid.nl</a> and during one of the sessions I saw <code>publiccode.yml</code> files in several repositories. Since I didn't know what <code>publiccode.yml</code> was, I decided to look into it.</p>

      <h2>What is publiccode.yml?</h2>
      <p>My initial thought was that <code>publiccode.yml</code> could be a way to standardize metadata for public open source software projects, making them more discoverable. But it turned out to be slightly different from what I expected...</p>

      <p><code>publiccode.yml</code> is a <strong>metadata standard</strong> designed specifically for software developed by or for <strong>public administrations</strong>. It's a YAML file that is placed in the root directory of the repository. The file contains structured information about the software project, making it easy for both humans and machines to understand what the software does, who maintains it, and whether it might be suitable for reuse in other contexts.</p>

      <p>The standard is developed as an open collaboration across public administrations and is governed by the <a href="https://github.com/publiccodeyml/publiccode.yml/blob/main/governance/charter.md">publiccode.yml Working Group Charter</a>. A steering committee consisting of public administration representatives oversees its development to ensure it aligns with the needs of public agencies.</p>

      <p><code>publiccode.yml</code> is designed to be:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Human-readable</strong> - Easy for civil servants, developers, and decision-makers to understand</li>
        <li><strong>Machine-readable</strong> - Structured data that can be automatically processed and indexed</li>
        <li><strong>Platform-agnostic</strong> - Works regardless of whether you use GitHub, GitLab, Codeberg, or any other Git platform</li>
        <li><strong>Extensible</strong> - Can grow as the project evolves</li>
        <li><strong>International</strong> - Designed for global use with support for country-specific extensions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The structure of a publiccode.yml file</h2>
      <p>A <code>publiccode.yml</code> file contains various sections that describe different aspects of the software.</p>

      <p>Here's a real example of a <code>publiccode.yml</code> file that is used to describe the <a href="https://github.com/MinBZK/nl-wallet">NL Wallet</a> project:</p>

      <pre class="code"><span class="c"># publiccode.yml for NL Wallet</span>
<span class="k">publiccodeYmlVersion</span>: <span class="s">"0.5.0"</span>

<span class="k">name</span>: <span class="s">NL Wallet</span>
<span class="k">url</span>: <span class="s">https://github.com/MinBZK/nl-wallet</span>
<span class="k">landingURL</span>: <span class="s">https://minbzk.github.io/nl-wallet/</span>
<span class="k">softwareType</span>: <span class="s">standalone/mobile</span>
<span class="k">developmentStatus</span>: <span class="s">development</span>

<span class="k">platforms</span>:
  - <span class="s">android</span>
  - <span class="s">ios</span>

<span class="k">categories</span>:
  - <span class="s">identity-management</span>
  - <span class="s">digital-citizenship</span>

<span class="k">description</span>:
  <span class="k">nl</span>:
    <span class="k">shortDescription</span>: <span class="s">Een veilige digitale wallet voor Nederlandse burgers...</span>
    <span class="k">features</span>:
      - <span class="s">Digitale opslag van identiteitsdocumenten</span>
      - <span class="s">Selectieve attribuutdeling</span>
  <span class="k">en</span>:
    <span class="k">shortDescription</span>: <span class="s">A secure digital wallet for Dutch nationals...</span>
    <span class="k">features</span>:
      - <span class="s">Digital storage of identity documents</span>
      - <span class="s">Selective attribute disclosure</span>

<span class="k">legal</span>:
  <span class="k">license</span>: <span class="s">EUPL-1.2</span>

<span class="k">maintenance</span>:
  <span class="k">type</span>: <span class="s">internal</span>
  <span class="k">contacts</span>:
    - <span class="k">name</span>: <span class="s">Ministerie van Binnenlandse Zaken en Koninkrijksrelaties</span>
      <span class="k">email</span>: <span class="s">edi@minbzk.nl</span>

<span class="k">intendedAudience</span>:
  <span class="k">countries</span>:
    - <span class="s">NL</span>

<span class="k">localisation</span>:
  <span class="k">localisationReady</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">availableLanguages</span>:
    - <span class="s">nl</span>
    - <span class="s">en</span></pre>

      <p>For the full schema description, see <a href="https://yml.publiccode.tools/schema.core.html">yml.publiccode.tools</a>.</p>

      <h2>Why public administrations are using it</h2>
      <p>The adoption of <code>publiccode.yml</code> by public administration organizations is driven by several compelling benefits:</p>

      <p><strong>Enhanced Discoverability:</strong> Without proper metadata, finding relevant open source software can be difficult; publiccode.yml provides a standardized way to describe software, with public administrations like Italy (via <a href="https://developers.italia.it/">Developers Italia</a>), Germany (via <a href="https://opencode.de">opencode.de</a>), and the Netherlands (via <a href="https://developer.overheid.nl">developer.overheid.nl</a>) using it to build comprehensive catalogs.</p>

      <p><strong>Better Decision Making:</strong> It provides clear descriptions, development status, maintenance details, legal information, and technical specifications that allows non-technical stakeholders to quickly assess whether a software project might be suitable for their needs.</p>

      <p><strong>Platform Independence:</strong> Since <code>publiccode.yml</code> is a file in the repository, it's part of the codebase and moves with it wherever you host your code, unlike platform-specific metadata.</p>

      <p><strong>Standardization and Interoperability:</strong> It provides a common language for public administrations worldwide to describe their software, while allowing for country-specific extensions.</p>

      <p><strong>Support for Open Source Policies:</strong> It enables governments to find existing solutions before building new ones, provides the information needed to assess software quality, and supports transparency in software procurement.</p>

      <p><strong>Facilitating Collaboration:</strong> It makes it easier for different administrations to collaborate by clearly identifying maintainers, project status, and technical details.</p>

      <blockquote>
        If it is public money, it should be public code as well.
        <cite>— the Public Money, Public Code campaign</cite>
      </blockquote>

      <h2>Adoption Across Europe</h2>
      <p>The <code>publiccode.yml</code> standard is gaining traction across Europe:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Italy:</strong> Mandatory for all public software, with a <a href="https://developers.italia.it/">national catalog</a> built on it</li>
        <li><strong>Netherlands:</strong> Recommended standard for open source projects on <a href="https://developer.overheid.nl">developer.overheid.nl</a></li>
        <li><strong>Germany:</strong> Used by <a href="https://opencode.de">opencode.de</a>, the national open source registry</li>
        <li><strong>European Union:</strong> Recognized by the <a href="https://interoperable-europe.ec.europa.eu/collection/open-source-observatory-osor">Open Source Observatory (OSOR)</a> and included in the <a href="https://interoperable-europe.ec.europa.eu/eu-oss-catalogue">EU Open Source Solutions Catalogue</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tooling and Ecosystem</h2>
      <p>A growing ecosystem of tools supports the <code>publiccode.yml</code> standard, developed alongside the specification as reference implementations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/italia/publiccode-parser-go">publiccode-parser-go</a> - Go parser and validator. Reference implementation of the specification.</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/bfabio/publiccode-parser-php">publiccode-parser-php</a> - PHP library for parsing and validation</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/italia/publiccode-crawler">publiccode-crawler</a> - Crawler to discover and collect descriptor files for catalogs</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/italia/developers-italia-api">software-catalog-api</a> - RESTful API powering software catalogs</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/bfabio/publiccode-api-client">publiccode-api-client</a> - Command-line client for the catalog API</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/italia/publiccode-parser-action">publiccode-parser-action</a> - GitHub Action for validation</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/italia/publiccode-validator-api">publiccode-validator-api</a> - RESTful API for validating files</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Let's use it!</h2>
      <p>I'm a big fan of open source and open standards, and I think <code>publiccode.yml</code> is a great example of both. It provides a simple yet powerful way to describe software projects in a standardized format, making them more discoverable and reusable across public administrations.</p>

      <p>I hope more public administrations and FOSS developers adopt the standard, and that it continues to evolve to meet the needs of the community. <a href="https://github.com/publiccodeyml/publiccode.yml/discussions/327">Version 0.7</a> was just released today and the maintainers already are working on a <a href="https://github.com/publiccodeyml/publiccode.yml/tree/1.0-rc">1.0 release candidate</a>.</p>

      <p>If you're involved in public sector software development, I encourage you to explore <code>publiccode.yml</code> and consider using it in your projects.</p>

      <hr style="margin: 2rem 0; border: 0; height: 2px; background: var(--ink);" />

      <h2>References</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://yml.publiccode.tools/">publiccode.yml Standard Website</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/publiccodeyml/publiccode.yml">GitHub Repository</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://developer.overheid.nl/kennisbank/open-source/standaarden/publiccode-yml">publiccode.yml standard in the Dutch government developer portal</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://interoperable-europe.ec.europa.eu/collection/open-source-observatory-osor/publiccodeyml-standard">Interoperable Europe - publiccode.yml Standard</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://publiccode-editor.developers.italia.it/">publiccode.yml Editor</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://developers.italia.it/">Italy's Developers Portal</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://opencode.de">German opencode.de Registry</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="atags">
